          "kind": "class",
          "description": "Purpose: A button that allows the user to switch between light and dark themes.\nCategory: Layout, Content Display\nWhen to use: When you need to provide a way for users to toggle between light and dark themes.\nWhen not to use: When the application only supports a single theme.\nWorks with components: mc-top-bar\nAlternative component names: Theme Toggle, Dark Mode Switch, Light/Dark Mode Toggle\nExtra notes: Implementation additional step: this component requires that the application has two stylesheets linked in the document head with the following attributes: <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"path/to/light-theme.css\" media=\"prefers-color-scheme: light\"> or <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"path/to/dark-theme.css\" media=\"prefers-color-scheme: dark\">",
